               <head>Majma' al-bahrain</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Majmaʿ al-baḥrayn by Sulṭān Muḥammad Dārā Shukūh</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85194674 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115436 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008113170 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4088-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alternative" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656959.0x000001 viaf_27879596">Sulṭān Muḥammad Dārā Shukūh</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656959.0x000001 viaf_27879596" type="alternative">سلطان محمّد دارا شكوه</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21092">Majmaʿ al-baḥrayn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21092">مجمع البحرين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>
                           <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109389" type="org">Qādirī</name>
                           <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">ṣūfī</term> interpretation of Vedic philosophy or the <term xml:lang="en">vedanta</term> by the Timurid or Mughal prince, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656959.0x000001 viaf_27879596" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n81102519" role="aut">Sulṭān Muḥammad Dārā Shukūh</persName> (killed <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1069</date>/<date calendar="Gregorian">1658</date>), son of Emperor <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_13108102" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50002533" role="oth">Shāh Jahān I</persName> (d. <date calendar="Gregorian">1666</date>), completed with the support of his <term xml:lang="en">Brahmin</term> secretary, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_81402153" role="trl">Rāy Chandarbhān</persName>, in <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1065</date>/<date calendar="Gregorian">1654</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                        <p>Unfoliated or paginated</p>
                        <p>Vertically oriented <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">safīnah</term> format
                        </p>
                        <p>Clear <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">nastaʿlīq</term> tending to <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">taʿlīq</term>, written obliquely
                        </p>
                        <p>Hindi inscription on recto of first folio: na 236</p>
                     </note>
